d Auburn University |accessdate=June 6, 2012}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:98%\"\n! width = 5%  class=\"unsortable\" | '''Image'''\n! width = 30% | '''Scientific name'''\n! width = 30% | '''Common name'''\n! width = 10% | '''Family'''\n! width = 5% | '''Venomous to humans''' \n! width = 15% | '''Conservation<br>concern''' \n|-\n| [[File:Agkistrodon contortrix contortrix CDC-a.png|180px]] || ''[[Agkistrodon contortrix contortrix]]'' || southern copperhead || [[Viperidae]] || Yes || Lowest\n|-\n| [[File:Agkistrodon contortrix mokeson.jpg|180px]] || ''[[Agkistrodon contortrix mokasen]]'' || northern copperhead<br>highland moccasin || Viperidae || Yes || Lowest\n|-\n| [[File:Agkistrodon-piscivorus.jpg|180px]] || ''[[Agkistrodon piscivorus conanti]]'' || Florida cottonmouth<br>green-tailed moccasin || Viperidae || Yes || Lowest\n|-\n| [[File:Agkistrodon piscivorus leucostoma.jpg|180px]] || ''[[Agkistrodon piscivorus leucostoma]]'' || western cottonmouth<br>water moccasin || Viperidae || Yes || Lowest\n|-\n| [[File:Agkistrodon piscivorus piscivorus CDC.png|180px]] || ''[[Agkistrodon piscivorus piscivorus]]'' || eastern cottonmouth<br>water moccasin || Viperidae || Yes || Lowest\n|-\n| [[File:Carphophis amoenus amoenus.jpg|180px]] || ''[[Carphophis amoenus amoenus]]'' || eastern worm snake || [[Colubridae]] || No || Lowest\n|-\n| [[File:Midwestern worm snake.jpg|180px]] || ''[[Carphophis amoenus helenae]]'' || midwestern worm snake || Colubridae || No || Lowest\n|-\n||| ''[[Cemophora coccinea copei]]'' || northern scarlet snake || Colubridae || No || Lowest\n|-\n| [[File:Coluber constrictorPCCP20030613-1137B.jpg|180px]] || ''[[Coluber constrictor|Coluber constrictor constrictor]]'' || northern black racer || Colubridae || No || Low\n|-\n| [[File:Blackracer111805.JPG|180px]] || ''[[Coluber constrictor priapus]]'' || southern black racer || Colubridae || No || Low\n|-\n| [[File:Crotalus adamanteus (5).jpg|180px]] || ''[[Crotalus adamanteus]]'' || ea